9 SECTION 3. ORS 308A.707 is amended to read:
10 308A.707. (1) Notwithstanding ORS 308A.706, and except as provided in section 2 of this 2026
11 Act, additional taxes shall be imposed on land that is disqualified from small tract forestland as-
12 sessment under ORS 321.712 or 321.716. If after disqualification the land remains specially assessed
13 under a special assessment program described in ORS 308A.706 (1)(d)(A) to (D), (F) or (G), the ad-
14 ditional taxes shall be computed under subsection (2) of this section. If after disqualification the land
15 is not specially assessed under a program described in ORS 308A.706 (1)(d)(A) to (D), (F) or (G), the
16 additional taxes shall be computed under subsection (3) of this section.
17 (2)(a) The additional taxes for disqualified small tract forestland that is qualified for special as-
18 sessment under a program described in ORS 308A.706 (1)(d)(A) to (D), (F) or (G) shall be equal to
19 the difference between the taxes assessed against the land under ORS 321.700 to 321.754 and the
20 taxes that would have been assessed against the land:
21 (A) Under ORS 321.257 to 321.390, if the land is located in western Oregon; or
22 (B) Under ORS 321.805 to 321.855, if the land is located in eastern Oregon.
23 (b) The number of years for which additional taxes shall be calculated shall equal the lesser of
24 10 years or the number of consecutive years the land has been assessed as small tract forestland.
25 (3)(a) The additional taxes for disqualified small tract forestland that is not qualified for special
26 assessment under a program described in ORS 308A.706 (1)(d)(A) to (D), (F) or (G) shall be equal to
27 the sum of:
28 (A) The amount determined under subsection (2) of this section; and
29 (B) The difference between the taxes that would have been assessed against the land under ORS
30 321.257 to 321.390, if located in western Oregon, or ORS 321.805 to 321.855, if located in eastern
31 Oregon, and the taxes that would otherwise have been assessed against the land, for the lesser of
32 the number of consecutive years the land was forestland or five years.
33 (b) Notwithstanding paragraph (a)(B) of this subsection, if any provision of ORS 308A.700 to
34 308A.733 would cause the deferral or elimination of additional taxes that are imposed under ORS
35 308A.703 or 308A.712, that provision shall also cause the deferral or elimination of the additional
36 taxes imposed under paragraph (a)(B) of this subsection, under the same terms, requirements and
37 conditions that additional taxes under ORS 308A.700 to 308A.733 are deferred or eliminated.
38 (4) The additional taxes described in this section shall be imposed and collected at the same time
39 and in the same manner as additional taxes described in ORS 308A.703 are imposed and collected.
40 (5) The additional taxes described in this section shall be deemed assessed and imposed in the
41 year to which the additional taxes relate.
42 (6) The amount determined to be due under this section may be paid to the tax collector prior
43 to the time of the next general property tax roll, pursuant to the provisions of ORS 311.370.
44 (7) As used in this section, “forestland,” “western Oregon” and “eastern Oregon” have the
45 meanings given those terms in ORS 321.700.
