27 holder must either:
28 (A)(i) Have not been previously granted an extension of time for the permit; and
29 (ii) Submit a complete application to the department within the time fixed originally in
30 the permit to complete construction of proposed works and apply water beneficially; or
31 (B)(i) Have been previously granted an extension of time for the permit, including an
32 extension of time under section 27 (3), chapter 282, Oregon Laws 2025; and
33 (ii) Submit a complete application to the department within the time specified in the
34 previous extension to complete construction of proposed works and apply water beneficially.
35 (d) An extension of time under paragraph (b) of this subsection may not exceed seven
36 years from the date that the extension application is approved by the department.
37 (3) The holder of a permit for municipal use shall commence and complete the construction of
38 any proposed works within 20 years from the date on which a permit for municipal use is issued
